cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

This paper is about object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new representation of objects using sample points, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG) and involves training a model to learn how to arrange these points (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the semantic significance of these points, which relates to natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method on a benchmark dataset, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM).
